{% extends 'base.html.twig' %}

{% block title %}Programs · OIATC{% endblock %}
{% block description %}OIATC runs three programs that put Indigenous-led digital governance into use: Anishinaabemowin, Anokii, and community knowledge. Each has shipped work and a clear funding ask.{% endblock %}
{% block og_title %}OIATC programs{% endblock %}
{% block og_description %}Three programs that put Indigenous-led digital governance into use, each with shipped work and a clear funding ask: language, sovereign infrastructure, community knowledge.{% endblock %}
{% block body_class %}route-programs{% endblock %}

{% block head_styles %}{% include 'partials/funder-styles.html.twig' %}{% endblock %}

{% block content %}
<article class="fund-wrap">

  <p class="fund-eyebrow">OIATC</p>
  <h1>Three programs. One premise.</h1>
  <p class="fund-lede">The systems meant to serve First Nations are rarely chosen by them. Each program puts that right in a different place. All three have shipped work, and each page says what the next dollar unlocks.</p>

  <p class="fund-principle"><strong>Live does not mean finished.</strong> Everything here is still in progress; the label says whether you can use it today, not whether it is done.</p>
  <p class="fund-more__k" style="margin-top: var(--gap-4)">The stages</p>
  <div style="display: flex; flex-wrap: wrap; gap: 8px 18px; margin-top: 8px; font-family: var(--font-sans); font-size: 13px; color: var(--ink-2);">
    <span><span class="fund-stage fund-stage--idea">Idea</span> designed or proposed, not built yet</span>
    <span><span class="fund-stage fund-stage--build">Building</span> being built now, not yet a working unit</span>
    <span><span class="fund-stage fund-stage--proto">Prototype</span> a working proof of concept, not yet in community use</span>
    <span><span class="fund-stage fund-stage--live">Live</span> in real use now, on infrastructure the community controls</span>
  </div>

  <div class="fund-cards" style="margin-top: var(--gap-6)">
    <article class="fund-card fund-card--flag">
      <div class="fund-card__k"><span>Language · Flagship</span><span class="fund-card__badge">in build</span></div>
      <h3><a href="/anishinaabemowin">Anishinaabemowin</a></h3>
      <p>Language revitalization with consent infrastructure. A curated corpus now, Lesson 1 in prototype, language games <a href="https://minoo.live/games" target="_blank" rel="noopener">live on Minoo</a>, a talking doll now being built, and story nights to come, all on technology the community controls.</p>
      <a class="fund-card__unlock" href="/anishinaabemowin">What is built, and what funding unlocks &rarr;</a>
    </article>
    <article class="fund-card">
      <div class="fund-card__k"><span>Infrastructure</span></div>
      <h3><a href="/programs/anokii">Anokii</a></h3>
      <p>Community platforms built on Waaseyaa, designed to be Nation-governed. Two OIATC-run reference vantages run today, seeded from public information, with a regional coverage plan from Sault Ste. Marie to Sudbury to Manitoulin ready to fund.</p>
      <a class="fund-card__unlock" href="/programs/anokii">The reference vantages and the rollout plan &rarr;</a>
    </article>
    <article class="fund-card">
      <div class="fund-card__k"><span>Knowledge</span></div>
      <h3><a href="/programs/community-knowledge">Community knowledge</a></h3>
      <p>Plain-language explainers for members: where community data lives, and responsible AI in coursework. Living resources, kept current through a time-stamped news system.</p>
      <a class="fund-card__unlock" href="/programs/community-knowledge">The explainers and their reach &rarr;</a>
    </article>
  </div>

  <p class="fund-body" style="margin-top: var(--gap-5)">OIATC supports the independent, member-led Robinson Huron Treaty Members' <a href="https://rhtcircle.ca" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Transparency Circle</a>. We neither run it nor govern it.</p>

  <section class="fund-sec">
    <div class="fund-statement">
      <p>When communities choose and govern their digital systems, the systems fit. When the systems fit, services and language outcomes improve. We exist to make the first part true.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <div class="fund-more">
    <p class="fund-more__k">More</p>
    <div class="fund-more__links">
      <a href="/about">About OIATC</a>
      <a href="/support">Support and partner</a>
      <a href="/news">News</a>
    </div>
  </div>

</article>
{% endblock %}
